A vintage 1950s style illustration of a frustrated person standing before an enormous, imposing bureaucratic machine made of tangled pipes, conveyor belts, and spinning gears. The person holds a simple envelope, trying to feed it into a tiny slot, while the machine spits out endless paper forms from multiple chutes. The color palette features muted teals, mustard yellows, and warm browns typical of mid-century advertising art. The machine looms comically large against a simplified background, its complexity absurdly disproportionate to the simple task at hand. Small robotic arms extend from the contraption, each pointing in different directions or holding up clipboards.
